  "prompt": "Are there any hotels in Goa which could be safe for unmarried couples?",
  "response": "Yes, Goa has many hotels that are safe and friendly for unmarried couples. Here are some tips to ensure a comfortable stay:\n\n1. **Check for Couple-Friendly Policies**: Many hotels explicitly state their openness to unmarried couples on booking platforms like OYO, MakeMyTrip, or Airbnb. OYO, for instance, has a \"Couple Friendly\" filter.\n\n2. **Reviews and Ratings**: Look at recent reviews and ratings from other unmarried couples to ensure the hotel respects privacy and treats all guests equally.\n\n3. **ID Requirements**: Carry valid government-issued identification. Most reputable hotels require IDs for registration and ensure the safety and legality of your stay.\n\n4. **Privacy and Security**: Opt for hotels with good security measures and those that prioritize guest privacy.\n\nHere are a few hotels often recommended for unmarried couples in Goa:\n\n- **Vivanta Goa, Panaji**: Known for its hospitality and central location.\n- **The Park Calangute Goa**: Offers a lively atmosphere with direct access to the beach.\n- **The Lazy Frog, Carmona**: A cozy and intimate setting often preferred by couples.\n- **Radisson Goa Candolim**: Known for its comfort and couple-friendly policies.\n\nRemember, the local laws and hotel policies can vary, so it's always good to confirm with the hotel directly if you have any concerns.",
